WEBVTT

00:00:00.741 --> 00:00:02.383
Sleep.

00:00:02.383 --> 00:00:05.204
It's something we spend about
a third of our lives doing,

00:00:05.204 --> 00:00:08.525
but do any of us really understand what it's all about?

00:00:08.525 --> 00:00:10.740
Two thousand years ago, Galen,

00:00:10.740 --> 00:00:12.880
one of the most prominent medical researchers

00:00:12.880 --> 00:00:13.939
of the ancient world,

00:00:13.939 --> 00:00:16.258
proposed that while we're awake,

00:00:16.258 --> 00:00:19.620
our brain's motive force, its juice,

00:00:19.620 --> 00:00:22.190
would flow out to all the other parts of the body,

00:00:22.190 --> 00:00:26.204
animating them but leaving the brain all dried up,

00:00:26.204 --> 00:00:27.820
and he thought that when we sleep,

00:00:27.820 --> 00:00:30.358
all this moisture that filled the rest of the body